readability_reflection: Interpolation because it reduced the amount of quotations marks and minimized the confusion of quotation marks within concatenated strings.
comprehension_debugging: Concatenation impacted it by confusing me on whether or not a quotation mark should be in the output or not and added a lot of symbols that seemed unnecessary in comparison to interpolation.
preference_rationale: Interpolation. Concatenation would be helpful for certain instances, but concatenation can be useful in others. I chose interpolation because it felt easier to identify what the output would be in since brackets are rarely needed in output in comparison to maybe quotation marks.
learning_curve: I do not have much experience with interpolation, but I still found it easier to understand by the end than I did concatenation.
suggestions_improvement: No, I think they're pretty well defined already.
